title: Oh Do Kwan students compete in Southeast Open
text:
Oh Do Kwan students compete in Southeast Open Sunday, October 11, 2015 Comments 
Top Row (from left): Master Joaquin Bonilla; Darius Soto, Kayla Greene, Coach Bryce Bonilla, Cole Gerken, Javon Edwards and Master Allen Green; Bottom Row (from left): Daelyn Soto, Kruz King, Logan Jackson, Lindsey Jackson, Kareem Gibson, Casey Gerken, Alana Greene, Rob Ball. 
Students from Oh Do Kwanâ€™s Newnan school competed last weekend in the inaugural Southeast Open Taekwondo Championship held in Powder Springs, featuring both forms (poonsae) and sparring. 
Both Kruz King and Kayla Greene earned gold medals in both categories among 13 athletes that had top-three finishes in respective divisions. 
Also earning gold were Rob Ball (sparring), Casey Gerken (sparring), Cole Gerken (forms) and Alana Greene (forms). 
Silver medal winners included Javon Edwards (sparring), Casey Gerken (forms), Lindsey Jackson (sparring) and Darius Soto (Sparring). 
Bronze medal efforts came from Bryce Bonilla (sparring), Cole Gerken (sparring), Kareem Gibson (sparring, forms), Alana Greene (sparring), Logan Jackson (sparring) and Daelyn Soto (sparring). More
